<section sectnbr = "5B">
<servcat sctnbr = "05" scnbr = "02">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENCP70A5206025" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "03" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Gear Shift Shaft and Fork Inspection
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENCP70A5206016">Manual Transaxle Assembly Disassembly and Reassembly</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Using feeler gauge, check clearance between fork (1) and sleeve (2) and replace those parts if it exceeds limit.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Clearance “a” between fork and sleeve
</title>
<ptxt>
Service limit “a”: 1.0 mm (0.039 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01520068.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "68.442mm" ver = "01" gw = "121" gh = "177"/>
</figure>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Insert each gear shift shaft into case and check that it moves smoothly. If it does not, correct using oilstone, reamer or the like.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
